                    "company": "to-the-point-consultancy",
                    "description": "With a history in health related fields, and development work, and a Bachelors degree in Cultural Anthropology/Public Relations and a Masters degree in Medical Anthropology and Sociology, I am particulary interested in research addressing inclusion/exclusion practices. Additionally, I have developed a passion for communication especially targeting health workers. A few years ago I developed a course 'Training and Communication Skills' that has been delivered for the past three years in Nepal (BIKASH, Training Centre, Pokhara) and also once in Ethiopia (ALERT Training Centre, Addis Abeba). This year, in March 2009, I assisted in the faciltiation of a Training of Trainers Programme in the Netherlands. The programme was designed and delivered by ENABLEMENT, NL, headed by Huib Cornelije, who has vast experience in the field of disability and in particular Community Based Rehabilitation. My primary concern is to contribute to the building of effective communication and training methodologies for those engaged in health and social sciences.",
