                    "company": "Disability Studies in Nederland (DSiN)",
                    "description": "Engaged in two researches - the first an evaluation and exploratory study, looking into perceptions of so-called intellectually disabled people about a Buddy Project that was designed and implemented with the aim of increasing their meaningful participation in a Disability Conference in Amsterdam. Furthermore, this study explored perceptions about the concept of 'inclusion' in people living in a city aiming to become an Inclusive City - Almere, the Inclusive Stad'.\nThe second research explored the understandings of and readiness for inclusive and participatory approaches for the development and implementation of a National Disability Programme in The Netherlands. This research had an emphasis, but not exclusive focus, on people labelled as Intellectually Disabled.",
